<TITLE> PM summons WASA men over water-logging </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 28 (bdnews24.com)--Prime minister Sheikh Hasina on Tuesday summoned top Dhaka WASA officials to her office over the water-logging in the city, a WASA official said. WASA chairman Golam Mostofa and acting managing director Mahbubur Rahman and several others went to meet with her at about 3pm, deputy chief public information officer at WASA Afsar Uz Zaman Khan said. The call came shortly after the water-logging issue was discussed at a meeting between deputy commissioners and the prime minister earlier in the day, he said. Earlier state minister for local government Jahangir Kabir Nanak was at the WASA office from 9am to 3pm to look after the work to resolve water-logging in the city after overnight monsoon rains. Nanak told bdnews24.com: "The prime minister has called [us] at her office and we are going there." bdnew
